-- ─── 2. Cascade SQL dropdown consolidated entry ─────────────────────────
DECLARE @bCascSql NVARCHAR(MAX) = N'Cascade dropdown pattern: a child Select / DataRepeater / DataGrid is filtered by the value(s) selected in one or more PARENT fields. The relationship lives in widgetProps via `optionsDependsOn` (for Select / Radio / Checkbox) or `queryDependsOn` (for DataGrid / DataRepeater / DynamicLabel).

KEY MECHANICS:
- Parent field: must have its OWN options source (static `options` array OR `properties.optionsSql`) so the dropdown actually has values to pick.
- Child field: declares the parent key(s) it depends on.
- SQL placeholder: parent key in camelCase prefixed with `:`. Example — parent key `country_id` → SQL placeholder `:countryId`. The renderer auto-maps snake_case → camelCase parameter binding.
- Refresh trigger: child auto-refetches whenever ANY of its parents changes.
- Reset on parent change: child value clears so the user can pick a fresh value from the new option set.

CHILD FIELD SHAPES BY WIDGET:

(a) Select / Radio / Checkbox depending on a parent:
```json
{
  "key":"city",
  "type":"Select",
  "label":"City",
  "properties":{
    "optionsSource":"sql",
    "optionsConnectionKey":"DashboardDatabase",
    "optionsSql":"SELECT Id AS value, Name AS label FROM Cities WHERE CountryId = :countryId ORDER BY Name",
    "optionsDependsOn":["country_id"],
    "optionsReloadOnChange":true
  }
}
```

(b) DataRepeater / DataGrid / DynamicLabel filtered by parents:
```json
{
  "key":"scorecard_grid",
  "type":"DataGrid",
  "label":"Scorecards",
  "widgetProps":{
    "useSql":true,
    "dataSource":"sql",
    "connectionKey":"DashboardDatabase",
    "masterQuery":"SELECT * FROM Scorecards WHERE PlayerId = :playerId AND RoundId = :roundId",
    "queryDependsOn":["player_id","round_id"],
    "pageSize":50
  }
}
```

CANONICAL CHAINS:
- 2-level: Country → City. Parent Select with optionsSql for countries; child Select with optionsDependsOn:["country_id"].
- 3-level: Country → Province → City. Each level''s optionsDependsOn lists ALL upstream parents (not just the immediate parent) so the cascade resets cleanly: country reloads provinces, province reloads cities — and changing country auto-clears province AND city.
- Picker → Detail: Select PARENT → Select CHILD → DataRepeater DETAIL. The user PICKS (Selects) before the DataRepeater shows. Never make a DataRepeater an intermediate picker (DataRepeater is display-only — see widget-datarepeater).

DISPATCHER GUARDS (dispatcher rules in MF_AI_KB_Rules):
- DR-001 — DataRepeater missing masterQuery is rejected (would render forever-loading spinner).
- DL-001 — DynamicLabel missing useSql:true OR resultMode is rejected.
- Cascade parent missing options/optionsSql is rejected (parent would never have a value to cascade).

KEY VS CAMEL CASE BUG: write SQL placeholder in camelCase (`:countryId`) even though the field key is snake_case (`country_id`). The renderer normalizes. Writing `:country_id` in SQL works in some queries but fails when the connection driver strips underscores. Always camelCase.

VERIFICATION BEFORE EMITTING SQL: call `get_table_columns(tableName)` on EVERY table referenced in the SQL — never assume FK columns exist by name. Tables called Players / Rounds / Scorecards usually have FK columns in the SCORECARDS table, not the lookup tables.

SEE ALSO:
- cascade-2level — 2-level country→city template
- cascade-3level — country→province→city
- widget-datarepeater-cascade — DataRepeater binding to master query';

